{"questionId":"9068051","questionHtml":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" class=\"wrs_chemistry\"><mi>CFC</mi></math>s produce chlorine radicals. Write two successive propagation steps to show how chlorine radicals catalyse the depletion of ozone.</span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mi>Cl</mi><mo>·</mo><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>ClO</mi><mo>·</mo></math>&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" class=\"wrs_chemistry\"><mi>ClO</mi><mo>·</mo><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>·</mo><mo>→</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mi>Cl</mi><mo>·</mo></math><br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" class=\"wrs_chemistry\"><mi>ClO</mi><mo>·</mo><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>→</mo><mi>Cl</mi><mo>·</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p><em>Penalize missing/incorrect radical dot (∙) once only.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9068051","referenceCode":"20N.2.hl.TZ0.e(iii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"CFCs produce chlorine radicals. Write two successive propagation steps to show how chlorine radicals catalyse the depletion of ozone.","paper":"2","level":"hl","questionNumber":"e(iii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 14: Chemical bonding and structure","14.1 Covalent bonding and electron domain and molecular geometries","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 14: Chemical bonding and structure"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}